### **Conclusion:**

By switching to dynamic delegates and ensuring that functions are properly declared and bound, you should resolve the access violation error. Don't forget to mark your functions with `UFUNCTION()` when using dynamic delegates and always verify that your delegates are properly bound before executing them.

